<subSubSection id="E8ED556577003421309CF9624283BF5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" type="notes">
<paragraph id="504C200468767FAB14AC832754B3224A" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FEECF2E5717DBCC50843E7A54234903A" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">
All the above cited material corresponds to the subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="D1A440F5195BBACA9B5A6BF482144581" authority="longispinosus" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Ancistrocerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ancistrocerus longispinosus subsp. longispinosus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="longispinosus" subSpecies="longispinosus">
<emphasis id="84D09E18BEAC57D2348CC4C326A7FACB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Ancistrocerus longispinosus longispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(de Saussure, 1855). The first record of this species in Malta (
<bibRefCitation id="1399E25D76F022B6111D70DD9E41CEEA" author="Schembri, SP" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="90 - 93" refId="B16" refString="Schembri, SP, 1980. Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata). Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana 112 (4-6): 90 - 93" title="Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata)." volume="112" year="1980">Schembri 1980</bibRefCitation>
) was published as 
<taxonomicName id="3DB6CD5036DFB30A7EB5822899A2992E" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Ancistocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ancistocerus longispinosus subsp. hellenicus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="longispinosus" subSpecies="hellenicus">
<emphasis id="43011F0A01D3E7498F76923DBBE90FFF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Ancistocerus longispinosus hellenicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="2A1F23483A282CABDF2B617A58B1EE3A" originalValue="Blüthgen">Bluethgen</normalizedToken>
, 1957) a taxon which is no longer considered to be valid (
<bibRefCitation id="7C2EA463DC936F41C497E2B670407DD8" author="Gusenleitner, J" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" refId="B8" refString="Gusenleitner, J, 1995a. Bestimmungstabellen mittel- und suedeuropaeischer Eumeniden (Vespoidea, Hymenoptera) Teil 4: Die Gattung Ancistrocerus WESMAEL 1836 mit einem Nachtrag zum Teil 1: Die Gattung Leptochilus SAUSSURE. Linzer Biologische Beitraege 27/2: 753-775." title="Bestimmungstabellen mittel- und suedeuropaeischer Eumeniden (Vespoidea, Hymenoptera) Teil 4: Die Gattung Ancistrocerus WESMAEL 1836 mit einem Nachtrag zum Teil 1: Die Gattung Leptochilus SAUSSURE. Linzer Biologische Beitraege 27 / 2: 753 - 775." year="1995 a">Gusenleitner 1995a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="3F3A03E09021CE751A73CC4CFC11199C" class="Insecta" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. longispinosus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispinosus">
<emphasis id="FD064AE41CE8B5CC73CFBF2D65F88038" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">A. longispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed across southern Europe, from the Iberian Peninsula to European Turkey, and in Northern Africa (Carpenter, unpublished). Mature larvae were described by 
<bibRefCitation id="B43E947B3C966BF809CF364E56934496" author="Tormos, J" journalOrPublisher="Nouvelle Revue d' Entomologie (NS)" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="31 - 36" refId="B18" refString="Tormos, J, Asis, JD, Gayubo, , Torres, F, 1998. Description of the mature larvae of Ancistrocerus kitcheneri (Dusmet, 1917), A. longispinosus longispinosus (Saussure, 1885) and redescription of that of A. trifasciatus (Mueller, 1776). (Hymenoptera, Vespidae). Nouvelle Revue d' Entomologie (NS) 15: 31 - 36" title="Description of the mature larvae of Ancistrocerus kitcheneri (Dusmet, 1917), A. longispinosus longispinosus (Saussure, 1885) and redescription of that of A. trifasciatus (Mueller, 1776). (Hymenoptera, Vespidae)." volume="15" year="1998">Tormos et al. (1998)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
